\subsection{Principal ideal domain}
\begin{definition}\label{ring.principal_ideal_domain}
\uses{ring.integral_domain,ring.unique_factorization_domain}
A **principal ideal domain**, or PID, is an {{ KNOWL('ring.integral_domain', 'integral domain') }} $R$ such that every ideal of $R$ is of the form $\langle a\rangle$ for some $a\in R$.

Every such ring is a {{ KNOWL('ring.unique_factorization_domain', 'unique factorization domain') }}.
\end{definition}


